  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 11 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 3 critical, 15 high, 3 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and Timişoara Traian Vuia (TSR/LRTR); plus 15 other bases. 3 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, thunderstorm / convective risk and cold‑temperature performance penalties  — most notably around Vilnius (VNO/EYVI), M. R. Štefánik (BTS/LZIB) and Vienna (VIE/LOWW). Network hotspots: Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Vilnius (VNO/EYVI) and 6 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, cold‑temperature performance penalties and snow / blowing snow. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO) and 9 others.",
  "detail90": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 11 airports right now. Base airports (focus): London Luton (LTN/EGGW) — HIGH: strong gusts risk; cloud base around 700 ft | Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) — HIGH: freezing fog; cold-temperature performance penalties; visibility down to 500 m, cloud base around 400 ft | Timişoara Traian Vuia (TSR/LRTR) — HIGH: mist | Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI) — HIGH: strong gusts risk | Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) — HIGH: mist; strong gusts risk | Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) — HIGH: mist; snow; cold-temperature performance penalties and 12 others. Worst affected now: Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH) — CRIT: freezing fog; cold-temperature performance penalties; visibility down to 200 m, cloud base around 100 ft (drivers: low-visibility procedures (reduced capacity), runway visual range (RVR) constraints, approach minima limits) | Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA) — CRIT: snow; visibility down to 1.2 km, cloud base around 300 ft (drivers: low ceilings, snow/blowing snow) | Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM) — CRIT: fog; snow; cold-temperature performance penalties (drivers: cold-temperature performance penalties, low ceilings, fog/freezing fog) | Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO) — CRIT: fog; snow; cold-temperature performance penalties (drivers: cold-temperature performance penalties, low ceilings, fog/freezing fog) | Vilnius (VNO/EYVI) — CRIT: mist; snow; cold-temperature performance penalties (drivers: approach minima limits, cold-temperature performance penalties, low ceilings) | Bordeaux–Mérignac (BOD/LFBD) — CRIT: strong gusts risk (drivers: thunderstorm/convective risk) and 5 others. Changed since last run: Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Vilnius (VNO/EYVI), Bordeaux–Mérignac (BOD/LFBD), M. R. Štefánik (BTS/LZIB), Košice (KSC/LZKZ), Poprad-Tatry (TAT/LZTT), Glasgow (GLA/EGPF), Warsaw Chopin (WAW/EPWA) and 2 others.",
